- "shine like beacons" refers to datasets with high data quality;
- "high percentage of valid data" means `percent_valid_data > 0`;
- "minimal number of outliers" means `n_outliers < 10`;
- "top 10 datasets" refers to the datasets with the highest data quality rank.

- A deployment is a unique instance of a data processing or collection setup;
- Valid data refers to data points that are not NaN;
- NaN values are missing or undefined data points.

sql:
SELECT AVG(n_all) AS avg_n_all
FROM datasets
WHERE n_all > 100;

external_knowledge:
- "health of the data" refers to the `percent_valid_data` column, which indicates the percentage of valid data points in the dataset;
- "garden beds" metaphorically represent the datasets;
- "sprouted at least one plant" means the dataset has at least one data point (`n_all > 0`).

sql:
SELECT AVG(percent_valid_data) AS avg_percent_valid_data
FROM datasets
WHERE n_all > 0;

